 business summary manufactures and supplies consumable productsxerium technologies inc engages in manufacturing and supplying consumable products used in the production of pulp paper and paperboard nonwoven products bulding products and other specialty applicationsit operates through the following business segments machine clothing and roll coversthe machine clothing segment represents the manufacture and sale of synthetic textile belts used to transport paper along the length of papermaking machinesthe roll covers segment represents the manufacture and refurbishment of covers used on the steel rolls of a papermaking machinexerium technologies was founded in  and is headquartered in youngsville ncnumber of employees    persons sales per businesses deltausd in millionusd in millionmachine clothing roll covers  sales per regions deltausd in millionusd in millionnorth america europe asia pacific otherlatin america managers nameagesincetitlemark statonpresident chief executive officer  directorjames forbes wilson mbachairmanclifford e pietrafittachief financial officer  executive vice presidentwilliam butterfieldchief technology officer  executive vpapril hoxie foley mbaindependent directorjohn f mcgovernindependent directorjoseph j gurandianoindependent directorroger a baileyindependent directoralexander toeldte mbaindependent directormitchell i quain mbaindependent director equities vote quantityfloatcompanyowned sharestotal float share a        shareholders nameequitiesamerican securities llc  carl marks management co llc  tocqueville asset management lp  tpg group holdings sbs advisors inc  harold c bevis mba  wynnefield capital inc  greenhouse funds lllp  robotti  co advisors llc  skylands capital llc  the vanguard group inc   sector consumer cyclicalcyclical consumer products textiles  apparel  textiles  leather goods   textiles  leather goods  nec sector textiles  leather goods  nec st jancapitalization m xerium technologies inc teijin ltd  nanji ecommerce co ltd